11 postsecondary institution, subject to the approval of the institution's
12 management board, to seek a new institutional accreditor from a list of
13 accreditors recognized by the United State Department of Education or to seek
14 a new specialized accreditor from a list of specialized accreditors maintained by
15 the Board of Regents.
16 C. The Board of Regents, in coordination with the management boards,
17 shall develop a process of changing an institutional accreditor in a manner that
18 ensures that a public postsecondary institution remains accredited at all times
19 by an accreditor recognized by the United States Department of Education.
20 D. With respect to specialized accreditation of an individual program or
21 unit, the Board of Regents shall do all of the following:
22 (1) Identify a list of programs that require specialized accreditation for
23 each program or unit and a corresponding list of accreditors.
24 (2) Adopt policies, in coordination with the management boards, to
25 ensure that each program or unit requiring specialized accreditation remains
26 accredited at all times by an accreditor from the list of accreditors maintained
27 by the Board of Regents.
